SUMMARY:Pravāha 2026
DESCRIPTION:Born from a vision to unite masters and experimentalists on a single stage\, Pravāha debuted in 2024. The second edition of this festival\, The Body As Space\, explores how we experience the world through sight\, sound\, touch\, taste\, and smell. \nOver eight days\, the festival becomes a journey through sensation. Classical melodies meet olfactory landscapes. Contemporary dance transforms into tactile dialogue. Installations immerse you in sound\, scent\, and memory itself. Conversations uncover India’s forgotten sensory archives and trace the origins of instruments that changed how we listen. \nWe invite you to tune into what you’ve always carried: the intelligence of your body\, the stories held in your senses. \nRSVP for the events you’d like to attend here. \nFestival Schedule: \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDate\nEvent\nArtist\nNature\nTimings\n\n\nFeb 22 – Mar 1\nHistories of Indian Perfume\nOn a Scented Trail\nThe Marg Foundation\nExhibition\n11am – 9pm\n\n\nFeb 22 – Mar 1\nFirst-Hand\nA Multisensorial Pause for Rest\, Attention\, and Care\nFor Ages 15+\nNitish Jain\nPaticipatory Immersive Experience\nFeb 22 – 11am\, 3pm\, 7pm\nFeb 23 – 3pm\, 7pm\nFeb 24 – 3pm\, 7pm\nFeb 25 – 3pm\, 7pm\nFeb 26 – 3pm\, 7pm\nFeb 27 – 3pm\, 7pm\nFeb 28 – 11am\, 3pm\, 7pm\nMar 1 – 11am\, 3pm\, 7pm\n\n\nFeb 22\nVāsané\nOlfactory Archives of Bangalore\nIndu Antony\nLecture Demonstration\n11:30am – 1pm\n\n\nFeb 22\nGrounded: A Food and Body Coffee Lab\nA Sensorial Exploration of Coffee\, Memory\, and Land\nShubhra Chatterji\nWorkshop\n4pm – 6:30pm\n\n\nFeb 22\nTHOL\nReconstructing Tamil Antiquity Through Revived Instruments and Contemporary Songwriting\nUrupaanar\nPerformance\n7pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nFeb 23\nCall of the Flute\nA Coming Together of Pichwai Paintings\, Kuchipudi Dance\, and Flute\nAmrita Lahiri\, Shan Bhatnagar & Hrishikesh Majumdar\nPerformance\n7pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nFeb 24\nNotes That Linger\nSounds and Scents Mingling in the Evening Air\nKarl Lutchmayer\nImmersive Performance\n7pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nFeb 25\nThe Far Post\nPhysical Theatre With Masks\, Puppetry and Music\nFor Ages 12+\nYuki Ellias\, Priyanshu Gupta\, Sumaiya Merchant\, Mati Rajput\, Arnob Bal\, Phalguni Vittal Rao\, Priyanka Babbar & Sanket Parkhe\nPerformance\n7pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nFeb 26\nNavrasa and I\nReliving the Rasas Through Raagas\nIndrayuddh Majumdar & Roopak Kallurkar\nPerformance\n7pm – 9pm\n\n\nFeb 27\nA Woman Or Not to Be\nA Bold Reimagining of Shakespeare’s Hamlet Through the Eyes of a Woman\nFor Ages 12+\nAdishakti Laboratory for Theatre Art Research\nPerformance\n7pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nFeb 28\nThe Percussive Pathway\nA Brief Foray into the Wondrous World of Percussion\nRahul Vanamali\nInteractive Performance & Workshop\n11am\n12:30pm\n2:30pm\n4:30pm\n\n\nFeb 28\nMaking the Ephemeral\nHistories of Indian Perfume\nJames McHugh\, Giti Datt & Ahalya Matthan\nDiscussion\n11:30am – 1pm\n\n\nFeb 28\nKadahin Milandaasin |\nڪڏهن ملنداسين\nA Jazz Quartet Weaving Memory into Music\nTarun Balani\, Sonja Ott\, Siddharth Gautam & Luke Marantz\nPerformance\n7pm – 8:30pm\n\n\nMar 1\nFuture Food Taste Test\nWhat’s in Our Climate Pantry?\nEdible Issues\nWorkshop\n4pm – 6pm\n\n\nMar 1\nAbhijñānaśākuntalam: The Circle of Love\nA Kūṭiyāṭṭam Performance Where Love Blossoms\nNepathya\nPerformance\n7pm – 9pm\n\n\n\nPresented by: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/pravaha-2026/
