SUMMARY:First-Hand
DESCRIPTION:First-hand. First\, Hand. \nAn experience that begins with the hand\, with touch. The most direct sense through which we connect with the world. \nBlindfolded\, headphones on\, you’re guided through forests\, seas\, and desert plains for 90 minutes. The world arrives through your fingertips: unexpected textures and sensations that reorient you. Your hands doing the work your eyes usually do. Through evocative storytelling\, you traverse sensory worlds shaped by the intelligence and wonder of the animal kingdom. \nAn invitation to attune yourself differently. To recalibrate away from the visual tyranny of screens and return to your body’s older\, quieter ways of knowing the natural world. \nPlease Note: Limited to 10 participants per session. \nSession Schedule:\nSun\, Feb 22 | 11am\, 3pm & 7pm\nMon\, Feb 23 | 3pm & 7pm\nTue\, Feb 24 | 3pm & 7pm\nWed\, Feb 25 | 3pm & 7pm\nThu\, Feb 26 | 3pm & 7pm\nFri\, Feb 27 | 3pm & 7pm\nSat\, Feb 28 | 11am\, 3pm & 7pm\nSun\, Mar 1 | 11am\, 3pm & 7pm \nProduction Credits:\nCreated by: Nitish Jain in collaboration with Studio MoreThanThat\nDramaturgy: Mara Ingea\, Katja Vaghi\, Anne Decker and Bhaskar Singh Thakur\nMusic: Raaghav Dhingra\nNarration: Anushri Patel\nCostumes: Emmanouela Mastora\, GulSohrab Studio\nArtists: Bhaskar Singh Thakur\, Zaid Khan\, Anukriti Mishra and Nitish Jain\nProduced by: Studio MoreThanThat\nCommissioned by: Rohini Nilekani Philanthropies\nThe project is made possible with the financial support of: Aparna Piramal Raje; Nova Sit (Czech Cultural Network); Studio Alta\, Prague; Scouts Institute Prague; Surnadal Billag AS\, Norway; Centro Jobel\, Italy; and Culture Moves Europe\, Belgium. \nPart of Pravāha 2026\, The Body As Space: A Journey Through The Senses. This year’s festival is built around what we hear\, smell\, touch\, taste\, and see. Eight days of multisensory experiences through classical music\, contemporary dance\, installations\, and conversations. \nPresented by: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/first-hand/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Experience,Performing Arts,Pravaha,Theatre
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail_thumbnail.png
END:VEVENT
