UID:85864-1772391600-1772398800@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:Abhijñānaśākuntalam: The Circle of Love
DESCRIPTION:Kālidāsa never met Kūṭiyāṭṭam. Until now. \nNepathya presents a scene from Abhijñānaśākuntalam\, Kālidāsa’s most celebrated play: the moment when Duṣyanta and Śakuntalā meet and fall in love. Conceived and designed by Guru Margi Madhu Chakyar\, this adaptation brings together what history kept apart. \nIn this adaptation\, the Sūta enacts Duṣyanta’s actions. Duṣyanta mirrors the deer. His responses echo Śakuntalā’s movements. What emerges is emotions synchronizing across bodies\, a complementary interplay that grew from attempting the impossible. \nKūṭiyāṭṭam stretches time. A gesture can last minutes. A glance becomes an entire emotional landscape. What you see is intensity\, immediacy\, and a particular kind of attention. \nKālidāsa. Kūṭiyāṭṭam. They meet at last. \nPart of Pravāha 2026\, The Body As Space: A Journey Through The Senses. This year’s festival is built around what we hear\, smell\, touch\, taste\, and see. Eight days of multisensory experiences through classical music\, contemporary dance\, installations\, and conversations. \nPresented by: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/abhijnanasakuntalam-the-circle-of-love/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Culture,Experience,Literature,Performing Arts,Pravaha,Theatre
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/thumbnail_The-Circle-of-Love.png
END:VEVENT
