UID:86149-1772476200-1772481600@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:Design\, Skills\, and Transcontinental Flair
DESCRIPTION:For over forty years\, legendary British designer Dame Zandra Rhodes and Indian design visionary Rajeev Sethi have shared a rare creative partnership rooted in friendship\, curiosity\, and cross-cultural exchange. From the landmark Festival of India exhibitions to collaborations with artisans across the subcontinent\, their work has reimagined how traditional craft\, contemporary design\, and global aesthetics can meet. \nIn this special conversation\, Rhodes and Sethi reflect on journeys through India’s textile traditions\, experiments that bridged craft and couture\, and the communities of makers whose skills shaped their work. They will discuss the evolving role of design in sustaining cultural heritage\, the transformative power of collaboration\, and the personal bond that has sustained their creative dialogue across decades. \nRich with stories of travel\, experimentation\, and shared vision\, this session offers a rare glimpse into a friendship that helped reshape global conversations around craft\, fashion\, and cultural diplomacy. \n  \nImage Credits\nAll images in the posters and header are from early photographs of Zandra Rhodes and Rajeev Sethi preparing for the Festival of India in 1981. \n  \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/design-skills-and-transcontinental-flair/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Design,Textiles,Visual Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail-16-3.jpg
END:VEVENT
